Issues.Body:
### Overview of the problem

This is about Bulma CSS framework.

Basically, there is a button on my electron app whose style and icon depend on the state. When the state changes, the style changes, but the icon remains the same. This icon is added via fontawesomeicon.


### Steps to Reproduce

1. First add Bulma via CDNJS to your react app.
```
<link
  rel="stylesheet"
  href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/bulma/0.7.4/css/bulma.min.css"
/>
<script defer src="https://use.fontawesome.com/releases/v5.3.1/js/all.js"></script>
```

2. Then add a component where a state change triggers a change in an icon for a button:
```
renderTabButton = () => {
    console.log("inside renderTabButton");
    if (this.state.tabLoaded === true) {
      console.log("inside tabLoaded true");
      return (
        <div className={classes.SaleDetailsHeaderContainer}>
          <button
            className={["button", classes.SaveTabButton].join(" ")}
            onClick={e => {
              this.setState({
                ...this.state,
                tabLoaded: !this.state.tabLoaded
              });
            }}
          >
            <span className={classes.IconContainer}>
              <i className="far fa-check-circle fa-3x" />
            </span>
            <span className={classes.Header}>Save Tab</span>
            <span className={classes.Empty} />
          </button>
        </div>
      );
    } else {
      console.log("inside tabLoaded false");
      return (
        <div className={classes.SaleDetailsHeaderContainer}>
          <button
            className={["button", classes.SelectTabButton].join(" ")}
            onClick={e => {
              this.setState({
                ...this.state,
                tabLoaded: !this.state.tabLoaded
              });
            }}
          >
            <span className={classes.IconContainer}>
              <i className="fas fa-clipboard fa-3x" />
            </span>
            <span className={classes.Header}>Select Tab</span>
            <span className={classes.Empty} />
          </button>
        </div>
      );
    }
  };
```

### Expected behavior

Button style should change, as well as the icon.

### Actual behavior

Only the button style changes. The fontawesomeicon remains the same.

### Possible solution (?)

Switching the script on the docs for:
```
<link rel="stylesheet" href="https://use.fontawesome.com/releases/v5.7.2/css/all.css" integrity="sha384-fnmOCqbTlWIlj8LyTjo7mOUStjsKC4pOpQbqyi7RrhN7udi9RwhKkMHpvLbHG9Sr" crossorigin="anonymous"
```
Seems to have solved the problem.

 This is about the Bulma **CSS framework** 

### Overview of the problem

I'm using Bulma **version** 0.7.4
My **browser** is: Chrome 72

### Description

 I am using create-react-app 2.
 I successfully managed to change navbar breakpoint using this:

```

 $navbar-breakpoint:300px;

@import '../node_modules/bulma/bulma.sass';
```

However, I had impression from reading elsewhere that I had to import first the file in which the variable I wanted to modify was located in (in this case navbar sass file)

```
@import "bulma/sass/utilities/_all.sass";
@import "bulma/sass/components/navbar.sass";
 
$navbar-breakpoint:300px;

@import '../node_modules/bulma/bulma.sass';
```
Which is the correct approach?

PS They both work in the sense that burger menu is shown only on <300px, however with the _second approach_ some shadow appears for the navbar too for certain screen widths.

